task.summary: Default task
* HoughLineLogicModule: created 'canny' picture using some lightness threshold; For the own spectrometer hough lines ate applied successfully now
* ImageSpectrumAcquisitionLogicModule.acquire(): removed hard-coded stuff
* RascalLogicModule: started evaluating RASCAL algorithm
* RascalLogicModule: peaks are detected now very fine when restricting supplied spectrum to nanometers smaller than 650 nm
* SpectrometerRegionOfInterestLogicModule: detect vertical bounding lines
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: started RASCAL integration
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: RASCAL integration; spectra are now required in burst mode and each step the detected peaks (of the averaged and smoothed spectrum) are shown

* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: RASCAL integration failed; Now we use a fixed number of most prominent peaks and verify (todo) against the difference to an according look-up table of intensities
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: started with PeakSelectionLogicModule
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: continued with SpectralLineSelectionLogicModule; gotta two lines detected successfully
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: SpectralLineSelectionLogicModule now detects the five most characteristic spectral lines
* SpectrometerWavelengthCalibrationLogicModule: integrated into GUI
